Reviews of the Spectrum edition were very positive; ''[[Your Sinclair]]'''s "Joystick Jury" rated it a "hit", citing its impressive graphics, and a structure that, while logical, provided a high level of replayability, as each game ended differently.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.users.globalnet.co.uk/~jg27paw4/yr08/yr08_59.htm|title=Your Spectrum 08 - Joystick Jury|publisher=|accessdate=27 June 2015}}</ref> It was also the winner of a ''[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]]'' Reader's Award for "Best Strategy and Simulation". The magazine commented positively on the graphics, partly because the visual style was "suited to a game set in the roaring twenties";<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crashonline.org.uk/12/awards.htm|title=CRASH 12 - Readers' Awards|publisher=|accessdate=27 June 2015}}</ref> this was despite "Mugsy" having to take place before 1919, since that is when its sequel, ''[[Mugsy's Revenge]]'', begins.

